<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3156324" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="1"><variable id="change_title"><link href="text/shared/guide/change_title.xhp" name="Changing the Title of a Document">Changing the Title of a Document</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3152801" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="3">You can specify a title for your document. Some file manager utilities can display the titles next to the filenames of your documents.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3156136" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="U" oldref="4">How to change the title of the current document</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3153345" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">Choose <emph>File - Properties</emph>. This opens the <emph>Properties of</emph> dialog.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3156410" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="6">Select the <emph>Description</emph> tab.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147242" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="7">Type the new title in the <emph>Title</emph> box and click <emph>OK</emph>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
</section>
